---
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets'

import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
import Hero from '../components/sections/Hero.astro'
import Section from '../components/Section.astro'
import heroImage from '../assets/images/hero/events.jpg'

import pic_starthere from '../assets/images/events/start_here.jpg'
import pic_action from '../assets/images/events/action.png'
import pic_panel from '../assets/images/events/propose_a_panel.jpg'
import pic_join from '../assets/images/events/join.jpg'
import pic_stage from '../assets/images/events/stage.jpg'

import LucideFile from '~icons/lucide/file'
import LucideDownload from '~icons/lucide/download'

const downloads = [
  {
    name: 'How to panel.pdf',
    size: '550.06KiB',
    link: 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1E3J7Lv-cWD1AeUnPLBSKTt5NeksQjRpd/view'
  },
  {
    name: 'How to panel.mkv',
    size: '145.76MiB',
    link: 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1leyocyV3Xlyk6f7wdllDIYZ4HGOmMGDO/view'
  }
]
---

<Base>
  <Hero headline="Enter the Fluufff game" image={heroImage}>
    <p>
      From cosy gatherings to high-energy stage moments, our activities and events are where the convention truly comes
      to life. Everything you see here is created by the community, for the community. Whether you're here to explore,
      meet new people, learn something new, or take the stage yourself, there is always something happening around you.
    </p>
    <p>
      Not sure where to start? You don't have to figure it all out right away. Just step in, look around, and follow
      what feels fun.
    </p>
  </Hero>
  <Section outerClass="bg-secondary-50">
    <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
      <Picture
        class="rounded-lg object-cover object-center h-full"
        src={pic_starthere}
        formats={['avif', 'webp']}
        fallbackFormat="jpg"
        alt=""
        widths={[400, 800, 1200]}
      />
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 justify-center order-2 lg:order-1">
      <h2 class="font-atari text-2xl md:text-3xl">New player? Start here</h2>
      <p>
        If this is your first time at Flüüfff, this section is for you. You do not need any experience to join
        activities. Many panels, workshops and events are beginner-friendly, and you are always welcome to simply sit
        in, watch, and get a feel for things first. There is no pressure to participate actively unless you want to.<br
        />
        Here's a quick idea of the activities and events you might encounter during the convention:
      </p>

      <section>
        <h3 class="uppercase text-xl md:text-2xl">Panels</h3>
        <p>Talks, discussions or presentations where people share ideas, stories or knowledge.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3 class="uppercase text-xl md:text-2xl">Workshops</h3>
        <p>Hands-on sessions where you can learn or create something together.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3 class="uppercase text-xl md:text-2xl">Meetups</h3>
        <p>Casual gatherings to connect with others who share your interests.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3 class="uppercase text-xl md:text-2xl">Big events</h3>
        <p>Games, competitions and larger activities that bring a lot of people together.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3 class="uppercase text-xl md:text-2xl">Stage performances</h3>
        <p>Everything from heartfelt moments to chaotic fun during events like Shownight.</p>
      </section>

      <p>
        Some activities may have limited space, but most are open to everyone. The full schedule will be announced
        closer to the convention date, so you can plan your adventure ahead of time or just decide on the spot.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>
  <Section grid="grid-col-1 text-center justify-items-center" gap="gap-4">
    <Picture
      class="w-2xs"
      src={pic_action}
      formats={['avif', 'webp']}
      fallbackFormat="jpg"
      alt=""
      widths={[200, 400]}
    />
    <h2 class="font-atari text-2xl md:text-3xl">Want to be part of the action?</h2>
    <p>
      You've seen the quests. You've met the players. You know what's possible.<br />
      Now imagine adding your own quest to the game.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can host your own panel, workshop or meet and greet, you can volunteer to team up with others to organize one
      of the really big events, or you can show your talents on stage as part of the Shownight.<br />
      Regardless if you want to do one or several of these, below you find more information and the corresponding forms.
      Hope to hear from you soon, Player 1!
    </p>
    <p>
      Unsure of how to plan and hold a panel? Feel free to check out this web lecture on how to panel and the
      corresponding presentation.
    </p>
    <section class="flex flex-wrap text-left gap-4">
      {
        downloads.map((d) => (
          <a
            href={d.link}
            class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-4 p-4 rounded-md bg-accent1-50 border border-accent1-200 no-underline text-nowrap"
          >
            <LucideFile />
            <div class="flex-1">
              <p class="font-bold">{d.name}</p>
              <p>{d.size}</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-4 rounded-md flex gap-2 border border-accent1-500 bg-neutral-50 items-center p-2 text-accent1-500">
              <LucideDownload />
              <p>Download</p>
            </div>
          </a>
        ))
      }
    </section>
  </Section>

  <Section outerClass="bg-secondary-50">
    <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
      <Picture
        class="rounded-lg object-cover object-center"
        src={pic_panel}
        formats={['avif', 'webp']}
        fallbackFormat="jpg"
        alt=""
        widths={[400, 800, 1200]}
      />
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 justify-center order-2 lg:order-1">
      <h2 class="font-atari text-2xl md:text-3xl">Propose your own panel</h2>
      <p>
        If you have an idea you want to teach, a project you want to show or a social event you want to organize, this
        is the form for you! Pitch your idea and we help you make it reality.<br />
        Once you fill in the form, 1 of our panel coordinators will contact you and help you get everything planned out properly.
        This person will also support you during the panel itself.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section>
    <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
      <Picture
        class="rounded-lg object-cover object-center"
        src={pic_join}
        formats={['avif', 'webp']}
        fallbackFormat="jpg"
        alt=""
        widths={[400, 800, 1200]}
      />
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 justify-center order-2 lg:order-1">
      <h2 class="font-atari text-2xl md:text-3xl">Team up with others to make one of the bigger events happen</h2>
      <p>
        A furry convention lives from big events like the Fursuit Games and fun competitions. These events need many
        paws to become reality, this is why we have this form! You just tell us which of the big events on our list you
        would like to help organize and we will put you together with other interested Furs to make it happen.<br />
        No worries, you will always have one of our panel coordinators to support you in the planning process and answer
        any questions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section outerClass="bg-secondary-50">
    <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
      <Picture
        class="rounded-lg object-cover object-center"
        src={pic_stage}
        formats={['avif', 'webp']}
        fallbackFormat="jpg"
        alt=""
        widths={[400, 800, 1200]}
      />
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 justify-center order-2 lg:order-1">
      <h2 class="font-atari text-2xl md:text-3xl">Show your talents on stage</h2>
      <p>
        Are you ready to take the stage and share something unique with our attendees? Do you have a quirky talent, a
        heartwarming story, or an unconventional performance that will leave a lasting impression? This is your chance
        to shine!
      </p>
      <p>
        You can propose a solo act or perform as a group, everything is possible, just let us know what you would like
        to show.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>
</Base>
